            <V n="text" t="variation">
              <U n="variation">
                <L n="variations">
                  <T>0xCDE137A8<!--It's best to make sure you are being romantic at the right moments. If either of you are in a bad mood, you might not find your romantic gestures going over too well. If either of you are feeling <B>Flirty</B>, though, then be proactive! Flirt like there is no tomorrow!--></T>
                  <T>0xB2EA4471<!--Pay attention to the discussion at hand. If you are listening closely to your partner you may be able know when the conversation has become <B>Unpleasant</B> or <B>Awkward</B>. Sometimes you just have to step away from each other and try again at another time.--></T>
                  <T>0x5EE94BAF<!--There are many different factors to having good romantic socialization with your partner! <B>Mood</B>, <B>Social Skills</B>, <B>Attraction</B>, and <B>Romantic Satisfaction</B> all can play a part. One might falsely think that a positive response from a romantic partner is somewhat random, but that's not true! So don't just do the same things over and over hoping for success, be mindful of everything that is happening in your experience!--></T>
                  <T>0x2B335CC0<!--Practice makes perfect! You have the ability to improve your skills in <B>Romance</B> or <B>Charisma</B>! You may even just talk to yourself in the mirror if all else fails. Becoming more socially skilled can do wonders for increasing your romantic comings and goings.--></T>
